In this article, President Obama announces the deployment of an additional 30,000 troops to Afghanistan in 2010. The purpose of these troops is to target the insurgency and secure key population centers, as well as train Afghan Security Forces and partner with them in the fight against the insurgency. The President emphasizes the international nature of the effort and calls for contributions from allies. He states that these additional troops will allow for a faster transfer of responsibility to Afghan forces, with the goal of beginning the transfer of US forces out of Afghanistan in July 2011. The President also highlights the importance of the Afghan government and people taking ultimate responsibility for their own country.